{NORTH expects to bid 2NT at his second turn, but SOUTH gives a positive 2\H 
response and his thinking changes! First he supports \Hs, setting the 
trump suit.

SOUTH then bids 3\S, showing first round control. NORTH tries 4NT (Blackwood) and 
SOUTH replies 6\C. This shows a \C void and one Ace, obviously the \SA.

NORTH bids 6\H, knowing they must lose the \DA.}

